The enigmatic brain disorder known as "mad cow disease" is causing
friction among European trading partners, and is threatening the 3.7
billion dollar British beef industry.  The British government insists
that the disease is not a threat to humans, but consumers are not
buying that argument. The British press has been making a big deal of
the Ministry of Agriculture's report that a Siamese cat had died of a
disease similar to "mad cow", saying that it proved that other
species, including humans, were vulnerable. West Germany and France
have banned the import of British beef.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d05"
TYPE="PERDOC"
SIZE="100"
DOCREF="WSJ910107-0139"
