SUMMARIZER="C"> 

The condition known in cattle as "mad cow disease", spongiform
encephalopathy, has shown up in Britain's sparsely scattered antelope
population. Over the past three years the disease has been diagnosed
in three elands, three kudu and an Arabian oryx. Since 1989 the
condition has also shown up in 34 cats and 29 goats. Only 348 cases of
sheep encephalopathy, or scrapie, were reported in 1990, as contrasted
with 894 cases in 1991. Since 1992 the British government has been
encouraging the reporting of scrapie to aid in the spongiform
encephalopathy research.</SUM>

<SUM
DOCSET="d05"
TYPE="PERDOC"
